 Since the transformation is monotone, we can solve 
\begin_inset Formula $y=e^{x}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 to get 
\begin_inset Formula $x=\ln y$
\end_inset

, giving 
\begin_inset Formula $dx/dy=1/y$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, for any 
\begin_inset Formula $y>0$
\end_inset

